---
import Layout from "@/layouts/page-layout.astro";
import NavLink from "@/components/nav-link.astro";
---

<Layout title="oai-pmh">
	<div class="mx-auto grid gap-4 content-center justify-center text-center py-8 px-15 h-full">
		<h1 class="font-extrabold text-lg md:text-5xl text-brand-800">
			Static OAI-PMH
			<br />
			<span class="text-base md:text-lg"
				>(Open Archives Initiative Protocol for Metadata Harvesting)</span
			>
		</h1>
		<div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-4 text-start">
			<div class="p-2 border rounded-md border-neutral-300 bg-brand-100">
				<h2 class="py-3 text-center text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-brand-800">
					About OAI-PMH
				</h2>
				<details open class="px-3 py-2 grid gap-2 text-justify">
					<summary>What is OAI-PMH ?</summary>
					<p>
						The <NavLink href="https://www.openarchives.org/pmh/"
							>Open Archives Initiative Protocol for Metadata Harvesting (OAI-PMH)</NavLink
						> is a widely used standard for sharing and collecting metadata between digital repositories.
						It enables libraries, archives, research projects, and other digital collections to make structured
						descriptions of their resources available in a machine-readable format.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details class="px-3 py-2 grid gap-2 text-justify">
					<summary>Why use OAI-PMH ?</summary>
					<p>
						By providing an OAI-PMH endpoint, our project allows external services to harvest
						metadata records of the manuscript descriptions and incorporate them into larger
						discovery platforms, catalogues, and research infrastructures. This helps increase the
						visibility, accessibility, and interoperability of our digital collection while allowing
						institutions to maintain control over their own data and websites.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details class="px-3 py-2 grid gap-2 text-justify">
					<summary>How it works ?</summary>
					<p>
						OAI-PMH operates through a set of standardized HTTP requests. A harvesting service sends
						a request to the repository's OAI-PMH endpoint and specifies an operation, known as a
						verb, using URL parameters. The repository then returns an XML response containing
						metadata or information about the collection.
					</p><p>
						The protocol defines six verbs: Identify, ListMetadataFormats, ListSets,
						ListIdentifiers, ListRecords, and GetRecord. These allow harvesters to discover
						information about the repository, retrieve lists of available records, or request
						individual metadata records. Because all OAI-PMH repositories use the same protocol,
						aggregators and discovery services can harvest metadata from many different collections
						in a consistent manner.
					</p>
					<p>
						In this implementation, the XML responses corresponding to the OAI-PMH verbs are
						generated during the website build process and made available as static resources. This
						provides a lightweight OAI-PMH interface while maintaining compatibility with standard
						harvesting workflows.
					</p>
				</details>
			</div>
			<div class="mx-auto border rounded-md w-full py-5 px-10 text-center">
				<h2 class="py-3 text-center text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-brand-800">Endpoints:</h2>
				<ul class="text-base/8 md:text-lg list-disc list-inside text-start">
					<li>
						<NavLink href="/oai-pmh/Identify.xml">Identify</NavLink>
					</li>
					<li><NavLink href="/oai-pmh/ListMetadataFormats.xml">ListMetadataFormats</NavLink></li>
					<li><NavLink href="/oai-pmh/ListIdentifiers.xml">ListIdentifiers</NavLink></li>
					<li><NavLink href="/oai-pmh/ListRecords.xml">ListRecords</NavLink></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
